and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:05,916 --> 00:00:06,984
(Scenes with child actors
followed production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,852 --> 00:00:09,453
Are you okay? My goodness.

5
00:00:09,453 --> 00:00:11,288
You should go see a doctor.

6
00:00:11,288 --> 00:00:12,323
I'm fine.

7
00:00:16,251 --> 00:00:17,385
we're almost there.

8
00:00:18,495 --> 00:00:20,130
We're here.

9
00:00:20,130 --> 00:00:21,131
- Go on inside.
- Okay.

10
00:00:25,302 --> 00:00:26,637
Thank you.

11
00:00:27,438 --> 00:00:28,239
I...

12
00:00:29,840 --> 00:00:31,709
I'm sorry about today.

13
00:00:32,510 --> 00:00:36,113
Being sick is nothing to apologize for.

14
00:00:36,547 --> 00:00:39,617
They say panic attacks come
without a warning.

15
00:00:40,851 --> 00:00:42,953
About that...

16
00:00:43,787 --> 00:00:45,890
I don't want my family to find out.

17
00:00:46,757 --> 00:00:47,858
I'm sorry.

18
00:00:49,793 --> 00:00:50,861
Boys.

19
00:00:51,662 --> 00:00:52,830
Mr. Seong.

20
00:00:53,797 --> 00:00:55,032
- What?
- Go on in.

21
00:00:57,835 --> 00:00:59,537
Why is it so quiet? Is no one home?

22
00:01:01,572 --> 00:01:02,573
This is our place.

23
00:01:02,573 --> 00:01:03,407
What?

24
00:01:04,608 --> 00:01:05,843
Were you robbed?

25
00:01:05,843 --> 00:01:08,245
Thief!

26
00:01:08,245 --> 00:01:09,747
My goodness.

27
00:01:10,648 --> 00:01:11,682
What?

28
00:01:14,785 --> 00:01:16,086
Wait.

29
00:01:16,086 --> 00:01:17,721
Shouldn't we report this?

30
00:01:17,721 --> 00:01:19,089
Come on.

31
00:01:19,089 --> 00:01:20,558
You think thieves are idiots?

32
00:01:20,558 --> 00:01:22,259
There's nothing here worth stealing.

33
00:01:27,631 --> 00:01:29,133
All the valuables are still here.

34
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,868
So there are things to steal here.

35
00:01:30,868 --> 00:01:32,036
Don't be so dense.

36
00:01:32,036 --> 00:01:32,870
The kids...

37
00:01:33,571 --> 00:01:35,072
The kids.

38
00:01:35,072 --> 00:01:37,274
(Baeju Public Bus Terminal)

39
00:01:39,276 --> 00:01:41,645
We're trying to get to Incheon.

40
00:01:44,114 --> 00:01:47,351
There's no direct bus to Incheon,
but there's one to Daegu.

41
00:01:48,185 --> 00:01:50,387
Can we get to Incheon from Daegu?

42
00:01:51,121 --> 00:01:52,122
Yes, you can.

43
00:01:52,857 --> 00:01:55,025
Then two tickets to Daegu, please.

44
00:02:01,565 --> 00:02:03,601
Why isn't Ji Sang answering his phone?

45
00:02:04,568 --> 00:02:07,605
- What happened here?
- There's a big mess in here too.

46
00:02:07,771 --> 00:02:08,839
Ji Cheon.

47
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:11,041
Are you with your brothers?

48
00:02:11,642 --> 00:02:15,145
(Baeju, Daegu)

49
00:02:27,925 --> 00:02:29,493
Right. My headphones.

50
00:02:30,828 --> 00:02:32,663
Seong Ji Gu, wait here.

51
00:02:32,663 --> 00:02:34,331
I'll go find my headphones and come back.

52
00:02:34,331 --> 00:02:35,266
Okay.

53
00:02:48,512 --> 00:02:51,649
I got home, but the kids were gone.

54
00:02:51,649 --> 00:02:53,817
The house is a complete mess.

55
00:02:53,817 --> 00:02:55,486
No, I can't reach them.

56
00:02:56,187 --> 00:02:56,954
Yes.

57
00:02:56,954 --> 00:02:59,156
Go talk to Dad right now.

58
00:03:01,759 --> 00:03:03,194
Were they looking for something?

59
00:03:03,194 --> 00:03:04,495
It looks like they packed their bags.

60
00:03:06,063 --> 00:03:08,132
They must've run away.

61
00:03:08,532 --> 00:03:09,466
Run away?

62
00:03:09,867 --> 00:03:10,768
What do I do?

63
00:03:12,036 --> 00:03:13,938
Shouldn't we report this to the police?

64
00:03:17,641 --> 00:03:18,809
Come on.

65
00:03:50,541 --> 00:03:51,375
They've sprouted.

66
00:03:52,476 --> 00:03:53,377
They've sprouted.

67
00:03:54,044 --> 00:03:56,647
I see cabbage sprouts.

68
00:03:58,349 --> 00:03:59,583
(Wife)

69
00:03:59,583 --> 00:04:00,951
This land isn't dead.

70
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:06,423
You clear the rocks,

71
00:04:07,658 --> 00:04:10,928
spread fertilizer,

72
00:04:11,562 --> 00:04:15,432
and wait. Then you succeed.

73
00:04:16,267 --> 00:04:18,035
- I did it.
- Dad.

74
00:04:18,035 --> 00:04:20,905
Son. The cabbage sprouted.

75
00:04:20,905 --> 00:04:23,140
I grew these sprouts.
I did it all by myself.

76
00:04:23,140 --> 00:04:24,708
I collected poop and...

77
00:04:25,876 --> 00:04:26,944
- Dad.
- Yes?

78
00:04:27,344 --> 00:04:28,479
Ji Sang and Ji Gu...

79
00:04:29,713 --> 00:04:30,881
They're gone.

80
00:04:30,881 --> 00:04:32,249
Sure.

81
00:04:32,249 --> 00:04:34,585
No. Ji Sang Gu...

82
00:04:35,286 --> 00:04:36,520
They're not home.

83
00:04:38,622 --> 00:04:39,456
What?

84
00:04:43,227 --> 00:04:44,094
The bus...

85
00:04:45,462 --> 00:04:46,597
Ji Gu...

86
00:04:47,498 --> 00:04:48,532
Ji Gu.

87
00:04:49,700 --> 00:04:50,701
Seong Ji Gu.

88
00:05:03,914 --> 00:05:04,915
Ji Sang.

89
00:05:08,953 --> 00:05:11,989
(Five minutes ago)

90
00:05:13,390 --> 00:05:14,658
The bus will depart now.

91
00:05:20,531 --> 00:05:22,399
My brother isn't here yet.

92
00:05:24,501 --> 00:05:26,704
He's my guardian,

93
00:05:26,704 --> 00:05:28,105
so I'll go get him.

94
00:05:28,339 --> 00:05:29,640
Please give me five minutes.

95
00:05:30,608 --> 00:05:32,510
We have to leave soon.

96
00:05:33,878 --> 00:05:35,713
You must hurry back, okay?

97
00:05:40,351 --> 00:05:41,352
Ji Sang.

98
00:05:43,687 --> 00:05:44,722
Ji Sang.

99
00:05:45,689 --> 00:05:47,291
It's time. Why aren't we leaving?

100
00:05:47,291 --> 00:05:48,592
Mister. Why aren't we leaving?

101
00:05:48,592 --> 00:05:51,428
- Why aren't we leaving?
- Why haven't we left yet?

102
00:05:51,428 --> 00:05:52,730
He needs to find his guardian.

103
00:05:53,564 --> 00:05:54,732
We have to go.

104
00:05:56,867 --> 00:05:57,868
We are departing now.

105
00:06:08,679 --> 00:06:09,513
Please...

106
00:06:11,916 --> 00:06:14,852
Your call is forwarded to voicemail...

107
00:06:16,854 --> 00:06:17,922
I'm doomed.

108
00:06:19,023 --> 00:06:25,196
(EP 3 Family, Family? Family!)

109
00:06:28,799 --> 00:06:29,900
(Second son)

110
00:06:35,406 --> 00:06:36,473
Ji Sang.

111
00:06:37,074 --> 00:06:38,242
Ji Gu.

112
00:06:41,545 --> 00:06:43,214
Those boys...

113
00:06:43,214 --> 00:06:45,449
They don't even know their way around.
Where did they go?

114
00:06:47,184 --> 00:06:49,753
All right. Thank you.

115
00:06:51,388 --> 00:06:54,425
He's saying that your brother got off
the bus to look for you.

116
00:06:56,694 --> 00:06:58,696
Where did Ji Sang go?

117
00:06:59,096 --> 00:07:03,167
(Baeju Public Bus Terminal)

118
00:07:05,769 --> 00:07:06,704
My goodness.

119
00:07:17,047 --> 00:07:18,015
Seong Ji Gu.

120
00:07:19,083 --> 00:07:20,117
Seong Ji Gu.

121
00:07:35,799 --> 00:07:36,767
What am I going to do?

122
00:07:38,002 --> 00:07:39,036
Carol...

123
00:07:45,843 --> 00:07:47,778
No, my phone.

124
00:07:47,778 --> 00:07:48,913
What do I do?

125
00:07:49,413 --> 00:07:52,016
Everything is going wrong today.

126
00:07:52,016 --> 00:07:54,251
Seong Ji Sang.

127
00:07:56,187 --> 00:07:58,656
Boys, where are you?

128
00:07:58,656 --> 00:08:00,658
You haven't found them yet?

129
00:08:00,658 --> 00:08:02,493
- My goodness.
- Where did they go?

130
00:08:03,761 --> 00:08:05,362
- Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo.
- What do I do?

131
00:08:05,362 --> 00:08:06,630
Let's not do this anymore.

132
00:08:06,630 --> 00:08:09,366
First, let's go to the village hall.

133
00:08:09,366 --> 00:08:11,936
We'll gather everyone
and come up with a plan.

134
00:08:11,936 --> 00:08:14,638
Seon Ja, get to the village hall
with Ms. Cho.

135
00:08:14,638 --> 00:08:16,774
I'll call everyone and meet you there.

136
00:08:16,774 --> 00:08:17,641
All right.

137
00:08:17,641 --> 00:08:18,742
- Go.
- Let's go.

138
00:08:19,577 --> 00:08:20,978
Everything will be okay.

139
00:08:20,978 --> 00:08:21,879
Let's go.

140
00:08:22,580 --> 00:08:23,747
My goodness.

141
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:32,056
This is your dear servant, Nam Hye Sun.

142
00:08:33,057 --> 00:08:35,459
The boys ran away. Where are you?

143
00:08:35,459 --> 00:08:38,495
Somewhere close to your heart.
I'm at the village hall.

144
00:08:39,330 --> 00:08:42,099
Did our goats run away again?

145
00:08:42,099 --> 00:08:43,133
That's a problem.

146
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:46,170
Mat Story's middle
and youngest children ran away.

147
00:08:47,171 --> 00:08:50,374
Every kid has a cell phone these days.

148
00:08:50,374 --> 00:08:52,810
They'll be back by dinner time.

149
00:08:52,810 --> 00:08:54,144
Forget it.

150
00:08:54,144 --> 00:08:55,713
They couldn't have gone far.

151
00:08:55,713 --> 00:08:57,114
First, make an announcement.

152
00:08:58,716 --> 00:09:00,251
It gets scary even in Yeonri-ri
after dark.

153
00:09:02,219 --> 00:09:03,621
Attention please.

154
00:09:04,421 --> 00:09:06,457
We are looking for two boys.

155
00:09:09,326 --> 00:09:10,127
Dad.

156
00:09:10,728 --> 00:09:12,296
Go to the village hall. I'll keep looking.

157
00:09:12,296 --> 00:09:13,497
Okay. Call me.

158
00:09:16,233 --> 00:09:18,035
I told him not to wander off.

159
00:09:19,036 --> 00:09:20,371
Hey, Seong Ji Gu.

160
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,508
What am I going to do?

161
00:09:27,811 --> 00:09:30,714
(Yeonri-ri Village Hall)

162
00:09:31,515 --> 00:09:32,483
Water.

163
00:09:35,519 --> 00:09:36,420
Honey.

164
00:09:36,854 --> 00:09:40,524
I was told that they got off
the school bus near here earlier.

165
00:09:41,225 --> 00:09:42,826
He probably went out with Ji Gu...

166
00:09:42,826 --> 00:09:44,395
Don't you know them at all?

167
00:09:44,595 --> 00:09:46,630
I think they ran away.

168
00:09:47,164 --> 00:09:49,700
What if something happened to them?

169
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:52,036
What are you talking about? Never.

170
00:09:52,036 --> 00:09:54,071
Please calm down and first...

171
00:09:54,071 --> 00:09:57,675
We should consider every possibility.

172
00:09:58,042 --> 00:10:01,011
Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo.
Please don't be too shocked.

173
00:10:02,513 --> 00:10:05,850
Let's confirm that this wasn't kidnapping.

174
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:06,784
Kidnapping?

175
00:10:06,784 --> 00:10:09,587
Did you receive any calls
from an unknown number?

176
00:10:12,923 --> 00:10:14,358
No. None.

177
00:10:14,358 --> 00:10:15,726
No.

178
00:10:15,726 --> 00:10:17,161
Then it's probably not kidnapping.

179
00:10:23,434 --> 00:10:24,368
Passports.

180
00:10:27,404 --> 00:10:29,139
They took their passports.

181
00:10:29,139 --> 00:10:30,507
Passports?

182
00:10:31,175 --> 00:10:32,109
Toronto?

183
00:10:32,810 --> 00:10:34,345
Airport?

184
00:10:34,345 --> 00:10:35,679
They must be crazy.

185
00:10:35,679 --> 00:10:36,814
What are we going to do?

186
00:10:36,814 --> 00:10:37,648
Listen.

187
00:10:38,182 --> 00:10:40,084
Mr. Kim told me...

188
00:10:40,084 --> 00:10:42,386
that he saw your sons running toward
the livestock barn earlier.

189
00:10:43,521 --> 00:10:44,889
Honey, go check. Hurry.

190
00:10:44,889 --> 00:10:46,790
- The barns?
- Go check it out, honey.

191
00:10:59,136 --> 00:11:00,137
My goodness.

192
00:11:00,704 --> 00:11:01,605
Are you okay?

193
00:11:02,473 --> 00:11:04,341
A father shouldn't get hurt.

194
00:11:04,341 --> 00:11:06,110
Ji Sang. Ji Gu.

195
00:11:07,478 --> 00:11:08,412
Ji Sang.

196
00:11:08,913 --> 00:11:10,414
- Ji Sang.
- Ji Gu.

197
00:11:10,981 --> 00:11:11,849
Ji Sang.

198
00:11:11,849 --> 00:11:12,950
Seong Ji Sang.

199
00:11:14,985 --> 00:11:16,520
Seong Ji Gu.

200
00:11:23,627 --> 00:11:24,461
Who is that?

201
00:11:25,262 --> 00:11:26,697
Officer Park.

202
00:11:32,169 --> 00:11:33,304
These are your kids, right?

203
00:11:34,238 --> 00:11:37,107
Who is this man? Why is he with my sons?

204
00:11:38,475 --> 00:11:41,145
The livestock barn owner
didn't recognize them...

205
00:11:41,145 --> 00:11:43,614
so he thought they were lost
and talked to them.

206
00:11:43,614 --> 00:11:44,915
I guess they asked him which way to go

207
00:11:44,915 --> 00:11:46,317
to catch a bus to the terminal.

208
00:11:47,718 --> 00:11:49,687
We thought it was a runaway case...

209
00:11:49,687 --> 00:11:52,223
What? Our kids ran away?

210
00:11:52,223 --> 00:11:53,891
We checked with the bus terminal.

211
00:11:53,891 --> 00:11:55,526
Ji Sang did buy bus tickets to Daegu,

212
00:11:55,526 --> 00:11:56,727
but neither of them got on the bus.

213
00:11:57,528 --> 00:12:00,364
Take your truck and head into town.

214
00:12:00,364 --> 00:12:01,799
I will search more thoroughly around here.

215
00:12:01,799 --> 00:12:03,534
Officer Park, keep me updated.

216
00:12:03,534 --> 00:12:04,301
- Okay.
- Okay.

217
00:12:06,503 --> 00:12:08,439
I think something happened
to the two of them.

218
00:12:08,439 --> 00:12:11,008
I have go there myself. I...

219
00:12:11,742 --> 00:12:14,378
As the mom, you should wait here.

220
00:12:15,279 --> 00:12:16,680
Let go of me.

221
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:19,149
I have to go find my kids.

222
00:12:19,583 --> 00:12:22,686
Where do you think you're going
in your condition?

223
00:12:24,054 --> 00:12:28,158
Chief. Come help me
talk her out of leaving.

224
00:12:28,158 --> 00:12:30,694
She's their mom.
She can't just stay here and wait.

225
00:12:30,694 --> 00:12:32,730
Get her a cab, and you stay here.

226
00:12:32,730 --> 00:12:34,064
The boys may come here.

227
00:12:34,398 --> 00:12:37,167
I'll go drive around that intersection.

228
00:12:37,167 --> 00:12:38,435
- I'll be back soon.
- Okay.

229
00:12:39,603 --> 00:12:40,871
- Please find them.
- Okay.

230
00:12:40,871 --> 00:12:42,740
- Search thoroughly.
- All right.

231
00:12:43,941 --> 00:12:45,042
Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo.

232
00:12:45,376 --> 00:12:47,645
Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo. Look at me, okay?

233
00:12:48,345 --> 00:12:50,614
If you're going to go, don't cry.

234
00:12:50,614 --> 00:12:52,016
Stay focused...

235
00:12:53,284 --> 00:12:55,619
and be sure to find them, okay?

236
00:13:03,227 --> 00:13:04,295
Seong Ji Gu.

237
00:13:11,001 --> 00:13:13,470
I've been here before.

238
00:13:16,574 --> 00:13:17,474
Ji Gu.

239
00:13:19,476 --> 00:13:20,344
Ji Gu.

240
00:13:23,013 --> 00:13:23,881
Ji Gu.

241
00:13:25,149 --> 00:13:26,283
Seong Ji Gu.

242
00:13:28,085 --> 00:13:29,486
Where are you?

243
00:13:33,357 --> 00:13:35,259
Where did Ji Sang go?

244
00:13:38,829 --> 00:13:40,798
(Baeju Public Bus Terminal)

245
00:13:44,201 --> 00:13:45,236
Ji Sang.

246
00:13:48,505 --> 00:13:50,207
Where is Ji Sang?

247
00:13:50,841 --> 00:13:51,675
Hey, kid.

248
00:13:52,309 --> 00:13:53,577
Are you looking for your mom?

249
00:13:54,245 --> 00:13:55,646
No.

250
00:13:55,846 --> 00:13:57,014
Hey.

251
00:14:00,885 --> 00:14:02,253
Were you separated from your mom?

252
00:14:02,453 --> 00:14:03,888
Do you know your mom's phone number?

253
00:14:04,588 --> 00:14:05,489
What's your name?

254
00:14:05,489 --> 00:14:06,991
You're lost, aren't you?

255
00:14:06,991 --> 00:14:08,926
No, I'm fine.

256
00:14:10,261 --> 00:14:11,328
Hey, kid.

257
00:14:12,496 --> 00:14:13,831
What's your name, kid?

258
00:14:14,298 --> 00:14:15,966
- I'm fine.
- Hey, where are you going?

259
00:14:17,801 --> 00:14:19,470
There are people looking for some kids.

260
00:14:51,702 --> 00:14:54,171
(Baeju Public Bus Terminal)

261
00:15:02,813 --> 00:15:03,714
Mom.

262
00:15:04,448 --> 00:15:05,316
Ji Sang.

263
00:15:05,683 --> 00:15:06,851
I miss you.

264
00:15:11,722 --> 00:15:12,723
I'm hungry.

265
00:15:22,032 --> 00:15:22,900
Ji Cheon.

266
00:15:23,467 --> 00:15:25,636
I heard from my mom
that your brothers are missing.

267
00:15:25,636 --> 00:15:26,904
They think the boys went to town.

268
00:15:26,904 --> 00:15:28,172
The buses aren't running. Hop on.

269
00:15:29,240 --> 00:15:30,107
Okay.

270
00:15:37,515 --> 00:15:38,782
- Hold on to me.
- What?

271
00:15:44,688 --> 00:15:46,457
If you don't hold tight, you'll fall.

272
00:15:46,457 --> 00:15:47,358
Hold on tight.

273
00:15:51,962 --> 00:15:53,564
My goodness.

274
00:15:55,099 --> 00:15:57,401
Maybe I should've gone with her
to find them.

275
00:15:57,401 --> 00:16:00,538
Maybe I shouldn't have said I'd wait here.

276
00:16:02,306 --> 00:16:04,441
Dong Sik, search the west side of town.
I'll search the east.

277
00:16:04,441 --> 00:16:05,676
Bo Mi, search around the school.

278
00:16:06,977 --> 00:16:08,312
Where did they go?

279
00:16:09,747 --> 00:16:10,648
Excuse me.

280
00:16:10,648 --> 00:16:12,783
Have you seen these kids?

281
00:16:12,783 --> 00:16:14,385
Have you seen these kids?

282
00:16:14,385 --> 00:16:15,486
Please take a look just once.

283
00:16:15,486 --> 00:16:16,253
Excuse me.

284
00:16:16,253 --> 00:16:18,556
One is in middle school,
and the other is in elementary.

285
00:16:18,556 --> 00:16:19,657
Have you seen them?

286
00:16:19,657 --> 00:16:22,860
Please take a good look.
They're my second and youngest sons.

287
00:16:22,860 --> 00:16:24,028
Ji Sang.

288
00:16:24,628 --> 00:16:26,030
Ji Gu.

289
00:16:26,030 --> 00:16:28,766
- Ji Sang. Ji Gu.
- Ji Sang.

290
00:16:28,766 --> 00:16:30,501
- Seong Ji Sang. Ji Gu.
- Ji Gu.

291
00:16:32,036 --> 00:16:33,003
Seong Ji Sang.

292
00:16:33,971 --> 00:16:35,005
Ji Sang.

293
00:16:35,005 --> 00:16:35,940
Seong Ji Gu.

294
00:16:35,940 --> 00:16:36,974
Ji Gu.

295
00:16:41,278 --> 00:16:42,146
I'm sorry.

296
00:16:42,146 --> 00:16:43,581
One moment please.

297
00:16:44,949 --> 00:16:46,083
Have you seen them?

298
00:16:46,784 --> 00:16:47,785
Wait.

299
00:16:49,553 --> 00:16:50,354
Ji Gu.

300
00:16:51,622 --> 00:16:52,456
Ji Sang Gu.

301
00:16:54,425 --> 00:16:55,926
I guess they didn't come to school.

302
00:16:57,061 --> 00:16:58,229
Come on, Ji Sang Gu.

303
00:17:10,107 --> 00:17:11,008
This...

304
00:17:12,109 --> 00:17:13,043
Ji Sang.

305
00:17:13,410 --> 00:17:14,311
Ji Gu.

306
00:17:14,912 --> 00:17:15,913
Seong Ji Sang.

307
00:17:18,015 --> 00:17:19,583
Have you seen this kid?

308
00:17:19,850 --> 00:17:22,286
He speaks with a Seoul accent,
and his height...

309
00:17:22,286 --> 00:17:24,421
- He's about this tall, right?
- About this tall.

310
00:17:25,322 --> 00:17:26,991
The kid who asked for directions.

311
00:17:26,991 --> 00:17:29,093
- You know him?
- Direction to where?

312
00:17:29,093 --> 00:17:30,160
He was asking how to get to Yeonri-ri.

313
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:32,096
Yeonri-ri. Goodness.

314
00:17:32,096 --> 00:17:33,097
That's great.

315
00:17:33,097 --> 00:17:34,598
Thank you.

316
00:17:34,598 --> 00:17:37,001
- Let's go.
- Where are they?

317
00:17:42,273 --> 00:17:43,173
Mr. Seong.

318
00:17:46,076 --> 00:17:47,845
Hey. That man...

319
00:17:48,679 --> 00:17:50,447
What is this?

320
00:17:50,447 --> 00:17:51,315
My goodness.

321
00:17:51,815 --> 00:17:54,018
Mr. Wang. My kids...

322
00:17:54,018 --> 00:17:55,186
No, don't cry.

323
00:17:55,920 --> 00:17:57,454
The part-timer said...

324
00:17:57,454 --> 00:17:59,490
your youngest asked for directions here.

325
00:17:59,490 --> 00:18:00,925
He couldn't have gone far.

326
00:18:00,925 --> 00:18:03,127
Which way did she say he went?
We have to go now.

327
00:18:03,127 --> 00:18:05,996
You can't drive
with your hands trembling like this.

328
00:18:05,996 --> 00:18:08,165
Seon Ja is the best driver.

329
00:18:08,165 --> 00:18:10,134
Where's your car? Let's go together.

330
00:18:10,134 --> 00:18:11,068
Give us your key.

331
00:18:11,068 --> 00:18:12,770
Please drive for me. It's this way.

332
00:18:12,770 --> 00:18:13,771
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

333
00:18:50,474 --> 00:18:51,609
What am I going to do?

334
00:19:11,161 --> 00:19:13,030
There he is. Over there.

335
00:19:14,899 --> 00:19:15,866
Wait.

336
00:19:17,167 --> 00:19:18,102
Wait.

337
00:19:20,070 --> 00:19:20,938
Wait.

338
00:19:23,007 --> 00:19:23,841
Hey, wait.

339
00:19:24,308 --> 00:19:25,809
Stop the truck.

340
00:19:25,976 --> 00:19:27,111
Stop the truck.

341
00:19:33,417 --> 00:19:35,786
What? What's he saying?

342
00:19:35,786 --> 00:19:37,755
Do you not see me?

343
00:19:40,891 --> 00:19:42,593
There's a kid in the back.

344
00:19:42,793 --> 00:19:44,161
Mister.

345
00:19:44,161 --> 00:19:45,829
Please help me.

346
00:19:45,829 --> 00:19:46,897
No.

347
00:19:46,897 --> 00:19:48,332
Stay inside.

348
00:19:48,966 --> 00:19:50,234
It's too dangerous. Stay inside.

349
00:19:50,768 --> 00:19:53,170
It's dangerous. Stay inside.

350
00:19:53,370 --> 00:19:54,805
Stop the truck.

351
00:19:54,805 --> 00:19:56,941
There's a kid in the back.

352
00:19:57,308 --> 00:20:00,211
Stop right there. Stop.

353
00:20:00,211 --> 00:20:02,213
Why isn't this going any faster?

354
00:20:02,213 --> 00:20:04,148
I can't lose the truck.

355
00:20:05,416 --> 00:20:06,317
Come on.

356
00:20:25,202 --> 00:20:28,906
Am I circling the same place?

357
00:20:31,041 --> 00:20:34,144
Why does this countryside feel bigger
than Canada?

358
00:20:35,479 --> 00:20:37,014
Where am I?

359
00:20:38,315 --> 00:20:40,618
Am I even headed
in the right direction to Yeonri-ri?

360
00:20:42,786 --> 00:20:43,954
Seong Ji Gu.

361
00:20:44,788 --> 00:20:47,258
You're smart, so you got home.

362
00:20:48,025 --> 00:20:49,059
Right?

363
00:20:57,835 --> 00:21:00,070
A ghost.

364
00:21:22,193 --> 00:21:23,427
What are you doing there?

365
00:21:26,964 --> 00:21:29,366
What's going on here?

366
00:21:29,767 --> 00:21:32,002
- Are you joking me?
- I'm sorry.

367
00:21:32,002 --> 00:21:33,671
I'll discipline him about this.

368
00:21:34,705 --> 00:21:35,839
Keep a better eye on the kid.

369
00:21:35,839 --> 00:21:37,708
I will. Thank you for everything.

370
00:21:39,043 --> 00:21:40,311
Goodbye.

371
00:21:45,583 --> 00:21:47,184
Are you okay? Are you hurt?

372
00:21:47,818 --> 00:21:48,752
You must've been really scared.

373
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:51,155
Why were you riding in a truck?

374
00:21:51,889 --> 00:21:54,258
I couldn't find my brother,

375
00:21:55,125 --> 00:21:57,194
and people kept telling me...

376
00:21:57,194 --> 00:22:00,464
that they would take me to my parents.

377
00:22:01,232 --> 00:22:02,533
So I was scared.

378
00:22:03,534 --> 00:22:05,436
You don't know how scary the world can be.

379
00:22:06,203 --> 00:22:08,005
You could've been in real danger.
You know that?

380
00:22:08,472 --> 00:22:09,874
Running away is serious,

381
00:22:09,874 --> 00:22:11,942
but getting into a stranger's truck
is even worse.

382
00:22:12,943 --> 00:22:14,345
I'm sorry.

383
00:22:18,148 --> 00:22:21,218
You should apologize to your parents.

384
00:22:23,721 --> 00:22:24,588
You've been through a lot.

385
00:22:25,789 --> 00:22:27,258
Let's go home now.

386
00:22:42,039 --> 00:22:43,908
Back in our day,

387
00:22:43,908 --> 00:22:46,076
running away from home was common.

388
00:22:46,610 --> 00:22:47,511
Right, Seon Ja?

389
00:22:48,345 --> 00:22:50,281
You call that a trend?

390
00:22:50,981 --> 00:22:52,016
Do they not know how dangerous it can be?

391
00:22:53,751 --> 00:22:55,286
How can they run away from home?

392
00:22:58,122 --> 00:22:59,823
I kept thinking on the way here.

393
00:23:01,325 --> 00:23:02,226
They ran away?

394
00:23:03,260 --> 00:23:04,094
Why?

395
00:23:05,262 --> 00:23:07,264
I tried to raise them
without depriving them of anything.

396
00:23:08,866 --> 00:23:11,602
But what parent truly knows
what's on their kid's mind?

397
00:23:13,370 --> 00:23:15,873
I heard you lived apart from them
for three years.

398
00:23:16,607 --> 00:23:19,276
Even when you live with them,
you don't know what they're thinking.

399
00:23:19,610 --> 00:23:21,278
If you lived apart,

400
00:23:22,847 --> 00:23:24,114
you'd know even less.

401
00:23:24,114 --> 00:23:27,852
Let's find the kids first
and take things slowly...

402
00:23:27,852 --> 00:23:30,087
Yes, I'm driving slowly right now.

403
00:23:30,721 --> 00:23:33,357
Seon Ja. A deer! Step on the brake!

404
00:23:36,994 --> 00:23:37,995
What?

405
00:23:43,267 --> 00:23:45,202
Ji Sang.

406
00:23:45,202 --> 00:23:46,570
- What?
- What?

407
00:23:48,005 --> 00:23:49,240
Ji Sang.

408
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:50,407
That's not a deer?

409
00:23:51,709 --> 00:23:52,610
Are you okay?

410
00:23:53,244 --> 00:23:55,246
- Dad.
- What happened to you?

411
00:23:55,246 --> 00:23:57,348
Everything's fine now.

412
00:23:57,348 --> 00:23:59,750
I'm here now. Everything's fine.

413
00:24:00,417 --> 00:24:03,621
- I'm sorry, Dad.
- It's okay.

414
00:24:03,621 --> 00:24:05,222
- I'm sorry.
- Everything's fine.

415
00:24:08,125 --> 00:24:09,360
Let's go see Mom now. It's okay.

416
00:24:11,529 --> 00:24:12,563
How touching.

417
00:24:20,271 --> 00:24:21,472
Attention, everyone.

418
00:24:22,339 --> 00:24:23,908
The kids have been found.

419
00:24:24,675 --> 00:24:26,777
They're on their way back home now.

420
00:24:27,178 --> 00:24:28,812
Even if you see them, look the other way.

421
00:24:28,812 --> 00:24:30,381
Act like nothing happened.

422
00:24:30,381 --> 00:24:31,549
Please do so.

423
00:24:32,483 --> 00:24:34,185
Once again...

424
00:24:34,752 --> 00:24:39,290
Everyone in Yeonri-ri,
you all did great work today.

425
00:24:42,626 --> 00:24:43,961
Seong Ji Gu.

426
00:24:43,961 --> 00:24:45,896
Do you know how worried I was?

427
00:24:46,463 --> 00:24:47,932
I'm sorry.

428
00:24:48,699 --> 00:24:50,134
Are you hurt?

429
00:24:51,769 --> 00:24:53,804
I missed you, Mom.

430
00:24:53,804 --> 00:24:55,673
I missed you too.

431
00:24:57,041 --> 00:24:58,175
My baby.

432
00:25:05,182 --> 00:25:06,016
Seong Ji Gu.

433
00:25:09,687 --> 00:25:10,788
Ji Sang.

434
00:25:13,023 --> 00:25:13,958
Ji Gu.

435
00:25:14,959 --> 00:25:16,560
Where were you?

436
00:25:17,828 --> 00:25:19,730
Do you know how much I looked for you?

437
00:25:23,300 --> 00:25:25,102
Are you okay, Ji Gu?

438
00:25:26,136 --> 00:25:28,272
It's okay. We're all here.

439
00:25:28,272 --> 00:25:30,808
We're all back together, safe and sound.
Everything will be fine.

440
00:25:30,808 --> 00:25:32,710
It's okay.

441
00:25:35,279 --> 00:25:37,548
Let's go home now.

442
00:25:38,382 --> 00:25:40,684
Those parents went through hell today.

443
00:25:42,686 --> 00:25:44,255
You should go home too.

444
00:25:44,255 --> 00:25:45,189
Okay.

445
00:25:45,422 --> 00:25:47,691
Thank you for today.

446
00:25:48,459 --> 00:25:50,528
- Thank you so much.
- Sure.

447
00:25:51,262 --> 00:25:53,597
Hey, boys. Don't ever do that again.

448
00:25:59,803 --> 00:26:00,938
Thank you.

449
00:26:00,938 --> 00:26:02,740
- Why are you out so late these days?
- Thank you.

450
00:26:02,740 --> 00:26:04,008
Come home earlier.

451
00:26:04,008 --> 00:26:04,842
What a beautiful night.

452
00:26:16,253 --> 00:26:18,189
Do you feel better now?

453
00:26:19,056 --> 00:26:20,257
Because of you,

454
00:26:20,891 --> 00:26:22,193
our whole family,

455
00:26:22,493 --> 00:26:25,429
and the entire village were worried sick.

456
00:26:25,429 --> 00:26:27,131
Are you happy that
your little brother cried his eyes out?

457
00:26:28,265 --> 00:26:30,134
Let's hear it then. What was the reason?

458
00:26:31,268 --> 00:26:32,770
Why were you...

459
00:26:32,770 --> 00:26:35,539
so desperate to go to Toronto?

460
00:26:38,242 --> 00:26:40,911
Carol has a new boyfriend.

461
00:26:40,911 --> 00:26:42,880
That darn Carol.

462
00:26:47,384 --> 00:26:48,919
You took your 9-year-old brother
with you...

463
00:26:49,486 --> 00:26:52,156
just go see a girl? That's so dangerous.

464
00:26:52,156 --> 00:26:53,057
You too.

465
00:26:54,191 --> 00:26:56,126
You came to Seoul without asking too.

466
00:26:57,561 --> 00:26:59,163
Did you ask us for our opinions, Dad?

467
00:26:59,830 --> 00:27:02,066
You said 'let's go' so we came here,
the middle of nowhere.

468
00:27:04,568 --> 00:27:06,670
So why can't I go? Why not?

469
00:27:06,670 --> 00:27:08,806
Don't you understand our situation?
How can you say that?

470
00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:11,609
I'm going crazy here.

471
00:27:12,309 --> 00:27:14,111
You're giving me a headache.

472
00:27:14,111 --> 00:27:15,546
You're such a problem child.

473
00:27:16,013 --> 00:27:17,181
I'm going crazy here.

474
00:27:17,181 --> 00:27:18,315
You always dote on Seong Ji Cheon.

475
00:27:19,683 --> 00:27:21,151
Then there's Ji Gu, Ji Cheon's clone.

476
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:24,321
You only need those two, right?

477
00:27:25,389 --> 00:27:26,357
I know it too.

478
00:27:28,492 --> 00:27:30,828
I'm just a problem child who can't even
get into a university in Seoul.

479
00:27:32,396 --> 00:27:34,865
I'm not smart like Ji Cheon or Ji Gu.

480
00:27:37,635 --> 00:27:39,270
You think I'm hopeless, don't you?

481
00:27:40,304 --> 00:27:41,505
I never...

482
00:27:43,340 --> 00:27:44,108
I...

483
00:27:46,210 --> 00:27:48,979
You misunderstood.

484
00:27:48,979 --> 00:27:50,714
I'm doing everything for you.

485
00:27:50,714 --> 00:27:51,582
For me?

486
00:27:53,083 --> 00:27:54,018
No.

487
00:27:54,985 --> 00:27:57,154
You're just ashamed of me.

488
00:27:58,055 --> 00:27:59,223
What are you talking about?

489
00:27:59,990 --> 00:28:02,493
What kind of parent would
be ashamed of their own child?

490
00:28:04,328 --> 00:28:05,229
Wait.

491
00:28:06,697 --> 00:28:08,799
Yes, you're right.

492
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:11,535
You're always chasing after some girl.

493
00:28:11,936 --> 00:28:14,572
Not only did you get expelled
because of her,

494
00:28:14,572 --> 00:28:16,173
but now you're trying to ruin
your whole life too?

495
00:28:16,974 --> 00:28:18,309
Do you think...

496
00:28:18,309 --> 00:28:20,978
I enjoy fighting with you like this
all the time?

497
00:28:20,978 --> 00:28:23,280
I'm doing this to help you
become a decent person.

498
00:28:23,814 --> 00:28:24,748
Then what?

499
00:28:25,316 --> 00:28:26,984
If I'm not a decent person, what am I?

500
00:28:27,985 --> 00:28:30,754
Am I a dog? Should I crawl on all fours?

501
00:28:31,522 --> 00:28:32,289
Son.

502
00:28:32,857 --> 00:28:35,326
You're the son of Cho Mi Ryeo
and Seong Tae Hun.

503
00:28:39,797 --> 00:28:40,931
I don't need that!

504
00:28:42,466 --> 00:28:43,367
That's...

505
00:28:44,735 --> 00:28:46,670
what I hate the most.

506
00:29:00,651 --> 00:29:01,485
It's okay.

507
00:29:02,953 --> 00:29:04,021
Calm down, honey.

508
00:29:05,022 --> 00:29:07,658
Ji Gu and Ji Sang's passports.

509
00:29:17,568 --> 00:29:20,504
Did your mother keep valuables like that?

510
00:29:21,205 --> 00:29:22,039
Yes.

511
00:29:23,107 --> 00:29:26,110
It's such an old-fashioned way,
the kids would never think to look here.

512
00:29:35,786 --> 00:29:36,787
Ji Sang...

513
00:29:39,323 --> 00:29:40,691
It's because of me, isn't it?

514
00:29:43,093 --> 00:29:45,196
Do you think I treat him unfairly?

515
00:29:46,964 --> 00:29:49,300
All kids are different.

516
00:29:49,300 --> 00:29:50,868
How can you raise them all the same way?

517
00:29:55,172 --> 00:29:56,307
That's easy for you to say.

518
00:29:57,675 --> 00:29:58,642
You see...

519
00:29:59,510 --> 00:30:02,513
Dong Sik and Seon Ja ran away from home
when they were young too.

520
00:30:02,513 --> 00:30:04,215
What happened today is nothing.

521
00:30:05,316 --> 00:30:06,116
You know what?

522
00:30:06,750 --> 00:30:08,819
I hate it when you
blurt things out like that.

523
00:30:10,754 --> 00:30:12,656
I'm always the villain
to the kids, aren't I?

524
00:30:13,257 --> 00:30:15,159
What have you been doing?

525
00:30:15,159 --> 00:30:17,528
If you hadn't been demoted,
would we even be here right now?

526
00:30:18,429 --> 00:30:20,130
What have I been doing?

527
00:30:20,865 --> 00:30:21,832
I hung in there.

528
00:30:21,832 --> 00:30:24,435
To give the kids good education
and feed them well.

529
00:30:24,635 --> 00:30:26,303
Do you think I enjoy living like this?

530
00:30:26,770 --> 00:30:30,207
You might've hung in there,
but I fell apart every single day.

531
00:30:30,207 --> 00:30:31,609
In a foreign country
where I didn't know anyone,

532
00:30:31,609 --> 00:30:33,143
with kids changing every day.

533
00:30:33,143 --> 00:30:35,546
Then you shouldn't have gone.
Did I force you to go?

534
00:30:35,546 --> 00:30:37,047
You chose to do it.

535
00:30:48,292 --> 00:30:49,093
Sure.

536
00:30:50,060 --> 00:30:51,428
It's all my fault.

537
00:30:52,530 --> 00:30:53,397
Wait.

538
00:30:55,266 --> 00:30:57,968
I'm sorry, honey.

539
00:30:58,569 --> 00:31:01,005
I'm sorry. That's not what I meant.
You know that.

540
00:31:01,005 --> 00:31:02,039
- Don't.
- Come on.

541
00:31:13,117 --> 00:31:14,118
Darn.

542
00:31:25,396 --> 00:31:26,697
I thought you ran away again.

543
00:31:34,605 --> 00:31:36,140
I'm sorry you didn't make it to Canada.

544
00:31:38,209 --> 00:31:39,343
I'm going tomorrow.

545
00:31:43,714 --> 00:31:45,482
It must be nice getting to do
whatever you want.

546
00:31:46,383 --> 00:31:47,651
Keep living like that.

547
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:50,721
You're cursing me, aren't you?

548
00:31:51,822 --> 00:31:52,756
It's a curse.

549
00:31:53,023 --> 00:31:53,991
I'm serious.

550
00:31:58,729 --> 00:32:00,464
But leave the house after you're grown up.

551
00:32:02,333 --> 00:32:04,201
If you leave now,
Mom and Dad will collapse.

552
00:32:44,375 --> 00:32:45,543
Honey?

553
00:32:46,877 --> 00:32:48,445
Cheon Sang Gu? What?

554
00:32:48,445 --> 00:32:50,314
'I completely screwed up
in raising my kids.'

555
00:32:50,314 --> 00:32:51,849
Have you ever thought that way?

556
00:32:52,583 --> 00:32:54,251
I don't remember.

557
00:32:54,251 --> 00:32:56,287
And you still call yourself
the head of this family?

558
00:32:57,054 --> 00:32:58,789
You deserve to be left alone in Korea.

559
00:32:59,223 --> 00:33:00,758
We're flying back to Canada.

560
00:33:04,461 --> 00:33:05,596
You fail as a father.

561
00:33:05,596 --> 00:33:06,564
No.

562
00:33:06,964 --> 00:33:08,566
I'll prove it with my cabbage.

563
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:10,935
You fail.

564
00:33:10,935 --> 00:33:11,969
You fail.

565
00:33:11,969 --> 00:33:16,473
- You fail.
- You fail.

566
00:33:16,473 --> 00:33:18,509
- You fail.
- You fail.

567
00:33:18,509 --> 00:33:21,145
- You fail.
- You fail.

568
00:33:26,250 --> 00:33:27,451
Cheon Sang Gu.

569
00:33:28,285 --> 00:33:29,153
Honey.

570
00:33:33,023 --> 00:33:34,391
Wake up, honey.

571
00:33:35,693 --> 00:33:38,562
Cabbage.

572
00:33:40,631 --> 00:33:41,465
Honey.

573
00:33:42,900 --> 00:33:44,535
You're not going to wake up?

574
00:33:44,768 --> 00:33:47,071
I don't want to be left alone in Korea.

575
00:33:47,705 --> 00:33:50,241
Honey, are you sick?

576
00:33:50,741 --> 00:33:52,977
Wake up. Let's go see a doctor.

577
00:33:53,577 --> 00:33:54,445
This isn't good.

578
00:33:54,945 --> 00:33:55,913
What did you say?

579
00:33:56,547 --> 00:33:57,648
I must...

580
00:33:58,816 --> 00:33:59,817
plow the field.

581
00:34:00,551 --> 00:34:02,086
Plow the field?

582
00:34:02,086 --> 00:34:03,654
I must plow the field.

583
00:34:04,488 --> 00:34:05,389
What?

584
00:34:07,391 --> 00:34:08,325
Hey.

585
00:34:08,626 --> 00:34:11,762
The guy from Mat Story...
How come he's not here yet?

586
00:34:13,230 --> 00:34:14,865
Did you go to Andromeda last night?

587
00:34:14,865 --> 00:34:16,033
Didn't you hear the announcement?

588
00:34:16,467 --> 00:34:19,003
We knocked ourselves out
with sleeping pills yesterday.

589
00:34:19,003 --> 00:34:20,471
How scary.

590
00:34:20,471 --> 00:34:21,972
Why? Can't you sleep well at night?

591
00:34:21,972 --> 00:34:24,708
Just a cup of makgeolli.

592
00:34:26,110 --> 00:34:28,045
How much did you drink?

593
00:34:29,747 --> 00:34:32,650
Last night, the Mat Story's kids ran away,

594
00:34:32,650 --> 00:34:33,551
and the whole village was in chaos.

595
00:34:33,551 --> 00:34:35,419
My goodness. Did you find them?

596
00:34:35,419 --> 00:34:36,687
Yes, of course.

597
00:34:36,687 --> 00:34:38,689
We blinked a few times and found them.

598
00:34:39,190 --> 00:34:40,191
They ran away?

599
00:34:41,325 --> 00:34:42,426
That's old-school.

600
00:34:42,426 --> 00:34:46,530
Even so, he shouldn't neglect the field.

601
00:34:47,565 --> 00:34:48,699
He must be sick.

602
00:34:49,567 --> 00:34:52,136
He must've collapsed from the shock.

603
00:34:52,336 --> 00:34:55,506
Kids and cabbage. You have to keep an eye
on them for them to grow well.

604
00:34:55,873 --> 00:34:57,308
I'm sure he'll come
after he checks on his kids.

605
00:34:57,308 --> 00:34:59,043
Leave him be. The field will be fine
for a day or two.

606
00:35:01,445 --> 00:35:03,714
What? His wife is coming.

607
00:35:10,421 --> 00:35:12,423
I'm sure it's around here somewhere.

608
00:35:13,624 --> 00:35:16,060
All these roads look the same to me.

609
00:35:20,798 --> 00:35:22,066
Good morning.

610
00:35:23,601 --> 00:35:24,535
Good morning.

611
00:35:31,609 --> 00:35:33,010
What? I thought this was his office.

612
00:35:45,956 --> 00:35:47,024
What is all this?

613
00:35:48,192 --> 00:35:49,059
My goodness.

614
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:51,529
When did he plant all these?

615
00:36:10,681 --> 00:36:13,751
Stop doing useless stuff and just rest.

616
00:36:20,124 --> 00:36:21,192
My goodness.

617
00:36:21,559 --> 00:36:24,695
He's about to go say hello
to the Grim Reaper.

618
00:36:25,296 --> 00:36:26,664
He's too weak.

619
00:36:27,231 --> 00:36:29,533
Let's just leave it with him and go.

620
00:36:29,533 --> 00:36:31,402
- Go.
- Okay. I'll be right back.

621
00:36:50,187 --> 00:36:51,922
Let's go. Let him rest.

622
00:36:54,124 --> 00:36:55,326
It's so hot.

623
00:37:12,209 --> 00:37:13,177
You poor thing.

624
00:37:15,513 --> 00:37:16,680
He's covered in sweat.

625
00:37:19,216 --> 00:37:20,117
What is it?

626
00:37:22,786 --> 00:37:23,988
I'm worried about Dad.

627
00:37:25,656 --> 00:37:27,591
Dad is sick. Go.

628
00:38:27,418 --> 00:38:28,686
I'm fine.

629
00:38:29,954 --> 00:38:30,888
I'm fine.

630
00:38:45,102 --> 00:38:48,272
Meet me at Dad's field after school today.

631
00:38:52,009 --> 00:38:53,644
So the rest of the field...

632
00:38:54,411 --> 00:38:56,180
I just make it look like this, right?

633
00:39:18,002 --> 00:39:19,003
I can do it.

634
00:39:20,604 --> 00:39:21,672
One, two, three.

635
00:39:23,841 --> 00:39:25,042
I'm doing it better than before.

636
00:39:30,915 --> 00:39:31,882
All this work...

637
00:39:33,250 --> 00:39:35,152
He's been doing it all by himself?

638
00:40:15,326 --> 00:40:16,193
Honey?

639
00:40:17,895 --> 00:40:18,762
Cho Mi Ryeo.

640
00:40:24,969 --> 00:40:25,836
Eat.

641
00:40:33,844 --> 00:40:36,146
Absolute rest until today.

642
00:40:48,225 --> 00:40:49,627
The house is a mess.

643
00:40:50,895 --> 00:40:53,330
Even if it's temporary, I should have
taken better care of the house.

644
00:41:25,262 --> 00:41:26,530
How amazing.

645
00:41:33,604 --> 00:41:34,538
No.

646
00:41:35,072 --> 00:41:36,840
How are we supposed to do all this?

647
00:41:37,875 --> 00:41:39,076
You must use your feet.

648
00:41:39,076 --> 00:41:42,012
You're supposed to use
your whole body to do this.

649
00:41:42,012 --> 00:41:43,948
You promised...

650
00:41:43,948 --> 00:41:45,549
to buy me a smartphone if I do this.

651
00:41:46,083 --> 00:41:47,284
We'll see.

652
00:41:47,284 --> 00:41:49,320
Why do you keep changing your words?

653
00:41:56,861 --> 00:41:59,496
You're good at digging.

654
00:42:02,032 --> 00:42:02,800
Me?

655
00:42:02,800 --> 00:42:05,035
You're good at this, Ji Sang.

656
00:42:06,437 --> 00:42:09,740
Ji Cheon. Come look at the row
that Ji Sang dug.

657
00:42:12,276 --> 00:42:13,677
I just did it.

658
00:42:15,012 --> 00:42:17,381
You did it way better than I did.

659
00:42:19,850 --> 00:42:21,886
Tell Dad to stop doing research.

660
00:42:22,253 --> 00:42:24,655
This isn't research.
It's just manual labor.

661
00:42:24,989 --> 00:42:26,190
Now you understand, right?

662
00:42:26,590 --> 00:42:29,393
Nothing in this world comes free.
Not one thing is easy.

663
00:42:29,960 --> 00:42:30,661
Keep digging.

664
00:42:33,163 --> 00:42:34,231
Mom.

665
00:42:35,099 --> 00:42:35,966
Yes?

666
00:42:39,003 --> 00:42:40,538
- By the way, Mom...
- Yes?

667
00:42:40,538 --> 00:42:42,806
What about Dad? Did he go see a doctor?

668
00:42:44,675 --> 00:42:46,877
No, he took his meds and is now resting.

669
00:42:47,211 --> 00:42:48,812
He'll go see a doctor tomorrow
if he needs to.

670
00:42:49,680 --> 00:42:50,848
By the way, Mom...

671
00:42:51,882 --> 00:42:52,950
To tell you the truth...

672
00:42:53,484 --> 00:42:54,285
Yes?

673
00:42:55,452 --> 00:42:57,221
I'm a little scared of Dad.

674
00:42:59,190 --> 00:43:00,624
Why are you scared of him?

675
00:43:01,025 --> 00:43:03,460
You know how much he loves you.

676
00:43:03,460 --> 00:43:06,630
But he always looks at me...

677
00:43:06,997 --> 00:43:09,500
with those triangle eyes.

678
00:43:09,500 --> 00:43:11,835
He's not doing that on purpose.

679
00:43:12,870 --> 00:43:14,138
It feels awkward.

680
00:43:15,272 --> 00:43:16,473
I feel uncomfortable.

681
00:43:22,680 --> 00:43:23,848
Ask him to play with you.

682
00:43:25,449 --> 00:43:27,151
That's a great idea.

683
00:43:27,718 --> 00:43:29,286
And...

684
00:43:29,286 --> 00:43:30,487
Your dad...

685
00:43:30,821 --> 00:43:32,990
is actually really cute.

686
00:43:38,062 --> 00:43:39,129
That's not...

687
00:43:39,129 --> 00:43:40,164
He's cute.

688
00:43:43,033 --> 00:43:44,535
My goodness.

689
00:43:48,372 --> 00:43:50,674
It's true.
Physical labor made my mind go blank.

690
00:43:50,674 --> 00:43:51,542
That's amazing.

691
00:43:53,043 --> 00:43:54,778
It was fun, wasn't it?

692
00:44:00,417 --> 00:44:02,219
We're not doing this
again tomorrow, are we?

693
00:44:02,219 --> 00:44:03,954
We agreed to help Dad out.

694
00:44:03,954 --> 00:44:06,257
I can't do it.

695
00:44:08,726 --> 00:44:09,793
Chief.

696
00:44:11,495 --> 00:44:12,830
Hello.

697
00:44:12,830 --> 00:44:14,498
Hi.

698
00:44:15,666 --> 00:44:18,736
Chief. Do you farm at home too?

699
00:44:19,603 --> 00:44:20,437
What?

700
00:44:21,138 --> 00:44:22,439
Come here, Ji Gu.

701
00:44:22,439 --> 00:44:23,474
This.

702
00:44:24,341 --> 00:44:26,744
Don't worry. I'll walk him home later.

703
00:44:27,011 --> 00:44:28,445
Goodbye. Don't worry about him.

704
00:44:34,051 --> 00:44:36,086
The cow dung smell is legendary.

705
00:44:36,854 --> 00:44:37,821
I'll shower first.

706
00:44:37,821 --> 00:44:39,356
No, you can't.

707
00:44:39,356 --> 00:44:41,692
I seriously feel like
I'm going to throw up. I'll go first.

708
00:44:44,028 --> 00:44:44,929
What?

709
00:44:47,398 --> 00:44:48,299
What's this?

710
00:44:49,300 --> 00:44:50,801
Did you work in the field?

711
00:44:51,302 --> 00:44:53,237
What did you do instead of resting?

712
00:44:54,004 --> 00:44:56,173
Did you clean all this?

713
00:44:56,774 --> 00:44:59,877
I felt a bit better,
so I cleaned up a little.

714
00:45:00,611 --> 00:45:01,745
I also made curry.

715
00:45:02,279 --> 00:45:03,981
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

716
00:45:05,449 --> 00:45:06,317
Go wash up.

717
00:45:07,017 --> 00:45:10,354
Everything here is for us to eat.

718
00:45:10,988 --> 00:45:12,890
The things that grow in the field
are for us to sell.

719
00:45:13,924 --> 00:45:16,160
I read somewhere that...

720
00:45:16,160 --> 00:45:18,462
the more microorganisms
there are in the soil,

721
00:45:18,462 --> 00:45:21,065
the better the crops grow.

722
00:45:21,065 --> 00:45:23,601
Do you take care of microorganisms, too?

723
00:45:24,735 --> 00:45:25,603
Microorganisms?

724
00:45:26,904 --> 00:45:28,606
Microorganisms.

725
00:45:28,606 --> 00:45:31,041
Right. We use compost. Fertilizer.

726
00:45:31,642 --> 00:45:33,010
Then...

727
00:45:33,377 --> 00:45:35,679
I heard that if you use compost tea,

728
00:45:35,679 --> 00:45:39,049
it reduces root stress. Is that true?

729
00:45:39,817 --> 00:45:43,120
I've never tried that before.

730
00:45:43,120 --> 00:45:44,188
I'll try it and let you know.

731
00:45:44,188 --> 00:45:46,857
You sure are curious, Seong Ji Gu.

732
00:45:46,857 --> 00:45:48,158
Are you going to be a farmer
when you grow up?

733
00:45:49,193 --> 00:45:53,230
Your field is full of cabbage,

734
00:45:53,230 --> 00:45:55,399
but cabbage doesn't grow well
in my dad's field.

735
00:45:56,166 --> 00:45:58,969
Did you go to the field today?

736
00:45:59,370 --> 00:46:03,007
Yes, I was just talking
while everyone else was digging.

737
00:46:03,274 --> 00:46:05,576
They said I will be digging plenty
once I grow up.

738
00:46:09,146 --> 00:46:12,416
Crops grow

739
00:46:12,416 --> 00:46:13,517
when they hear people's footsteps.

740
00:46:14,285 --> 00:46:15,953
If they hear people coming,
they can't help but grow.

741
00:46:16,887 --> 00:46:19,924
Can you go there with me again later?

742
00:46:20,824 --> 00:46:21,759
Why?

743
00:46:21,759 --> 00:46:23,761
I saw earlier that...

744
00:46:23,761 --> 00:46:25,596
some of them looked weak.

745
00:46:26,530 --> 00:46:28,399
I want them to hear our footsteps.

746
00:46:31,235 --> 00:46:34,471
If you don't sleep at night,
you won't grow either.

747
00:46:34,939 --> 00:46:36,173
That's not good.

748
00:46:36,840 --> 00:46:39,310
If neither I nor the cabbage grows,

749
00:46:39,310 --> 00:46:40,778
Dad will be sad.

750
00:46:48,552 --> 00:46:49,620
Good work today.

751
00:46:50,487 --> 00:46:52,289
Let's eat.

752
00:46:52,289 --> 00:46:53,157
Okay.

753
00:47:00,998 --> 00:47:03,601
Dad, this is really good.

754
00:47:03,601 --> 00:47:04,602
Really?

755
00:47:04,969 --> 00:47:06,537
Thanks, Ji Gu.

756
00:47:06,537 --> 00:47:08,839
But it's just because you're hungry...

757
00:47:08,839 --> 00:47:10,541
from all that labor.

758
00:47:11,509 --> 00:47:14,378
Did you eat curry every day?

759
00:47:16,347 --> 00:47:17,715
It goes well with kimchi.

760
00:47:18,315 --> 00:47:19,884
I ate rice with seaweed.

761
00:47:20,150 --> 00:47:22,486
When I got tired of that,
I ate rice with curry.

762
00:47:32,363 --> 00:47:33,664
My goodness.

763
00:47:35,966 --> 00:47:37,268
Look at the field.

764
00:47:38,736 --> 00:47:42,406
Did they plow the field or break it?

765
00:47:44,208 --> 00:47:45,209
My goodness.

766
00:47:51,081 --> 00:47:51,982
What's that?

767
00:47:56,720 --> 00:47:57,988
Goodness.

768
00:47:59,323 --> 00:48:02,359
His family worked hard,

769
00:48:02,927 --> 00:48:05,429
but all the seedlings will die
if they're left like this.

770
00:48:07,831 --> 00:48:09,733
Goodness.

771
00:48:11,635 --> 00:48:13,871
I just came out here to exercise, okay?

772
00:48:13,871 --> 00:48:15,973
I didn't come out here
to help you, Seong Tae Hun.

773
00:48:20,578 --> 00:48:23,881
A field comes back to life
along with people's footsteps.

774
00:48:24,682 --> 00:48:27,785
I felt bad seeing your wife
and kids working hard in the field,

775
00:48:31,055 --> 00:48:32,590
so I came out to exercise.

776
00:48:34,792 --> 00:48:37,828
I came to work my biceps, forearms,
and do some squats.

777
00:48:55,079 --> 00:48:56,146
Unbelievable.

778
00:48:57,014 --> 00:49:00,017
You and the kids were farming geniuses?

779
00:49:01,919 --> 00:49:03,387
We did a good job, didn't we?

780
00:49:06,323 --> 00:49:07,992
Seeing how hard you and the kids worked,

781
00:49:07,992 --> 00:49:09,527
I think I'm all better now.

782
00:49:12,329 --> 00:49:15,599
Ji Sang worked on that side of the field.

783
00:49:15,599 --> 00:49:17,434
I was surprised to see how good he was.

784
00:49:17,434 --> 00:49:18,335
Really?

785
00:49:24,175 --> 00:49:24,942
Honey.

786
00:49:25,509 --> 00:49:28,679
Let's not worry too much
about Ji Sang now, okay?

787
00:49:29,313 --> 00:49:30,381
Let's take it slow...

788
00:49:30,848 --> 00:49:35,052
and help him find what he's good at,
what he wants to do, okay?

789
00:49:36,086 --> 00:49:38,455
Even so, I'm sending him to college.

790
00:49:41,091 --> 00:49:43,460
Of course. He should go to college.

791
00:49:44,328 --> 00:49:46,030
Let's go inside.

792
00:49:51,135 --> 00:49:52,036
Honey.

793
00:49:52,403 --> 00:49:54,972
I think they grew
because we watered them yesterday.

794
00:49:54,972 --> 00:49:56,273
It's amazing.

795
00:49:56,273 --> 00:49:57,474
Of course.

796
00:49:57,775 --> 00:49:59,476
They don't grow on their own either.

797
00:49:59,476 --> 00:50:02,112
They only grow as much
as we care for them.

798
00:50:03,814 --> 00:50:04,949
Honey.

799
00:50:06,250 --> 00:50:08,819
Let's go visit the kids' school.

800
00:50:10,221 --> 00:50:11,055
Their school?

801
00:50:12,556 --> 00:50:15,593
In your right hand,
hold the pointed stick.

802
00:50:15,593 --> 00:50:17,795
In your left hand, hold the round stick.

803
00:50:18,128 --> 00:50:19,730
Deongdeok.

804
00:50:19,730 --> 00:50:21,765
Kungdeok kung. I'll demonstrate.

805
00:50:25,236 --> 00:50:26,904
Deongdeok kungdeok kung.

806
00:50:26,904 --> 00:50:28,339
Good. Deongdeok.

807
00:50:30,007 --> 00:50:34,979
Deongdeok kungdeok kung.

808
00:50:36,080 --> 00:50:38,082
He loves to read.

809
00:50:38,916 --> 00:50:39,750
Ji Gu.

810
00:50:40,985 --> 00:50:41,852
Seong Ji Gu.

811
00:50:42,753 --> 00:50:43,787
Son.

812
00:50:49,059 --> 00:50:52,830
(Cafeteria)

813
00:51:04,041 --> 00:51:05,075
Hello.

814
00:51:06,343 --> 00:51:07,311
Hello.

815
00:51:07,311 --> 00:51:10,214
Bo Mi. Thank you so much
for the other day.

816
00:51:10,214 --> 00:51:11,582
No, no.

817
00:51:11,582 --> 00:51:13,284
We didn't get to thank you properly
that day.

818
00:51:13,284 --> 00:51:14,418
You went through an ordeal, didn't you?

819
00:51:14,418 --> 00:51:15,953
Not at all. I didn't.

820
00:51:15,953 --> 00:51:18,322
Thank you so much for everything you did.

821
00:51:18,322 --> 00:51:19,823
There's no need.
You must've been quite worried.

822
00:51:19,823 --> 00:51:21,525
They left without a word.

823
00:51:21,525 --> 00:51:23,994
I was so shocked that I thought
my heart was going to drop.

824
00:51:23,994 --> 00:51:25,596
It's such a relief they were found.

825
00:51:25,596 --> 00:51:28,132
We are so grateful.

826
00:51:28,132 --> 00:51:30,100
I was so worried that I was terrified...

827
00:51:39,243 --> 00:51:40,277
Bo Mi.

828
00:51:42,346 --> 00:51:44,481
Are you getting ready to run away too?

829
00:51:44,481 --> 00:51:45,349
What?

830
00:51:45,749 --> 00:51:47,751
Why are you keeping secrets
from your family?

831
00:51:48,886 --> 00:51:49,920
You see...

832
00:51:49,920 --> 00:51:53,023
If those secrets pile up one by one,
they'll become really heavy.

833
00:51:53,023 --> 00:51:54,058
Do you want me to help a little?

834
00:51:55,292 --> 00:51:57,428
- Mat Story...
- No, Bo Mi. Please.

835
00:51:59,697 --> 00:52:00,564
Why?

836
00:52:00,564 --> 00:52:02,967
What's wrong with a med student
working part-time in a cafeteria?

837
00:52:04,268 --> 00:52:07,638
Things that are nothing
if you talk about them right away...

838
00:52:07,638 --> 00:52:09,506
keep growing inside if you bottle them up.

839
00:52:09,506 --> 00:52:11,275
When they finally explode,
it'll hurt even more.

840
00:52:17,248 --> 00:52:20,851
Why did your brothers run away?

841
00:52:21,418 --> 00:52:26,123
I guess Ji Sang's girlfriend
started dating another guy.

842
00:52:27,191 --> 00:52:28,926
So he said he had to go to Toronto.

843
00:52:29,994 --> 00:52:30,761
It's ridiculous, isn't it?

844
00:52:31,061 --> 00:52:33,464
No. I think it's cool.

845
00:52:34,098 --> 00:52:36,433
That little kid sure learned about love.

846
00:52:36,834 --> 00:52:39,270
What can he do about someone
who doesn't feel the same way anymore?

847
00:52:39,770 --> 00:52:41,105
Well...

848
00:52:41,972 --> 00:52:43,707
Isn't what I feel the most important?

849
00:52:44,275 --> 00:52:46,076
What I want to do,

850
00:52:46,076 --> 00:52:47,378
how I want to do it...

851
00:52:47,878 --> 00:52:49,547
Only I know that, right?

852
00:52:56,887 --> 00:52:58,389
- Honey.
- Yes?

853
00:52:59,156 --> 00:52:59,890
You see...

854
00:53:01,025 --> 00:53:01,992
Well...

855
00:53:03,260 --> 00:53:04,228
You see...

856
00:53:06,263 --> 00:53:08,098
Never mind. Let's go.

857
00:53:10,801 --> 00:53:13,537
It's nice coming
to the kids' school with you.

858
00:53:23,848 --> 00:53:25,149
To be honest,

859
00:53:26,851 --> 00:53:28,152
I have a condition.

860
00:53:28,986 --> 00:53:29,854
What?

861
00:53:30,688 --> 00:53:32,189
Are you sick?

862
00:53:34,225 --> 00:53:35,259
A butting-in condition.

863
00:53:37,962 --> 00:53:39,830
I couldn't help but notice it.

864
00:53:39,830 --> 00:53:42,299
When someone sits there all day
with such lonely eyes,

865
00:53:42,299 --> 00:53:43,934
my condition starts acting up.

866
00:53:45,302 --> 00:53:48,772
I don't have anywhere to go,
and I don't want to go home.

867
00:53:51,909 --> 00:53:53,077
I know a great place.

868
00:53:54,979 --> 00:53:56,247
Do you want to go pick apples?

869
00:53:56,547 --> 00:53:57,615
Apples?

870
00:54:14,098 --> 00:54:15,065
Do you like apples?

871
00:54:16,667 --> 00:54:17,535
I don't know.

872
00:54:19,904 --> 00:54:21,372
Try one. It's sweet.

873
00:54:30,147 --> 00:54:30,915
It's good.

874
00:54:32,316 --> 00:54:34,585
These are Gamong apples. They are amazing.

875
00:54:34,585 --> 00:54:36,887
Sometimes I come here to help out,

876
00:54:36,887 --> 00:54:39,390
and when they're in season,
I give them to the kids as snacks.

877
00:54:39,390 --> 00:54:40,324
So I know about these apples well.

878
00:54:40,991 --> 00:54:43,994
Was it always your dream
to be a nutritionist?

879
00:54:45,663 --> 00:54:47,231
I always wanted to cook.

880
00:54:47,765 --> 00:54:50,367
But while I was preparing
to become a chef, before I knew it,

881
00:54:51,202 --> 00:54:52,169
I ended up working at this school.

882
00:54:54,138 --> 00:54:56,207
Do you like what you do?

883
00:54:57,441 --> 00:54:58,809
Of course.

884
00:54:59,109 --> 00:55:01,812
I really love this job.

885
00:55:03,848 --> 00:55:05,649
When I see kids grow up
eating the food I make,

886
00:55:06,684 --> 00:55:08,018
I feel really proud.

887
00:55:10,487 --> 00:55:12,556
I don't know what I like.

888
00:55:14,291 --> 00:55:16,927
Is that really a problem?
That's actually a good thing.

889
00:55:17,995 --> 00:55:19,029
What's good about it?

890
00:55:20,164 --> 00:55:21,465
You can start figuring it out now.

891
00:55:22,266 --> 00:55:24,768
There's fun in searching, you know.

892
00:55:28,839 --> 00:55:31,375
You look happy.

893
00:55:32,276 --> 00:55:33,110
I like that.

894
00:55:37,781 --> 00:55:38,883
What I mean is...

895
00:55:39,750 --> 00:55:40,584
You see...

896
00:55:43,988 --> 00:55:44,855
I...

897
00:55:46,690 --> 00:55:47,658
have something to tell you.

898
00:56:21,692 --> 00:56:22,726
Get home safe.

899
00:56:28,866 --> 00:56:31,068
What we did today...

900
00:56:34,271 --> 00:56:35,239
A secret.

901
00:56:35,639 --> 00:56:36,640
Let's keep it a secret.

902
00:56:37,274 --> 00:56:38,375
Thanks for hanging out with me today.

903
00:56:39,376 --> 00:56:40,244
Here.

904
00:56:43,681 --> 00:56:47,251
I heard the scooter.
Why isn't she coming in?

905
00:56:47,251 --> 00:56:48,018
I don't know.

906
00:56:51,255 --> 00:56:53,257
Bo Mi, are you home?

907
00:56:54,925 --> 00:56:55,626
What?

908
00:56:56,927 --> 00:56:57,661
Hey.

909
00:57:00,598 --> 00:57:01,532
I should go now.

910
00:57:02,833 --> 00:57:03,734
Wait.

911
00:57:04,301 --> 00:57:05,269
I...

912
00:57:13,444 --> 00:57:17,081
Can we go to the apple orchard
again sometime?

913
00:57:25,155 --> 00:57:26,023
I'm off now.

914
00:57:32,696 --> 00:57:33,864
Yes, I'm home.

915
00:57:36,300 --> 00:57:38,435
You're home.

916
00:57:38,435 --> 00:57:40,571
- Bo Mi is home.
- Bo Mi is home.

917
00:57:41,238 --> 00:57:43,307
My treasure.

918
00:57:43,307 --> 00:57:45,409
Your mom and I were doing this. One, two.

919
00:57:45,409 --> 00:57:47,678
- Did you wait long?
- That's enough.

920
00:57:49,513 --> 00:57:50,814
Come here.

921
00:58:12,436 --> 00:58:13,470
I'm so proud of you.

922
00:58:14,505 --> 00:58:17,107
I roll around in the manure field for you.

923
00:58:17,908 --> 00:58:19,410
Wow. This is...

924
00:58:20,444 --> 00:58:21,545
What does it say?

925
00:58:34,658 --> 00:58:35,693
What's this?

926
00:58:48,873 --> 00:58:49,707
Dad?

927
00:58:51,976 --> 00:58:52,877
Seong Ji Cheon.

928
00:58:54,144 --> 00:58:55,746
What are you up to these days?

929
00:58:57,047 --> 00:58:57,915
What?

930
00:58:59,316 --> 00:59:02,119
You should be back in med school,
so what were you doing there?

931
00:59:03,521 --> 00:59:05,556
You saw me earlier?

932
00:59:06,123 --> 00:59:07,858
You see...

933
00:59:08,926 --> 00:59:11,695
I thought I would make some pocket money
by working part-time...

934
00:59:11,695 --> 00:59:13,097
Why are you lying to me?

935
00:59:13,864 --> 00:59:15,099
Then what is this?

936
00:59:23,707 --> 00:59:26,076
(Withdrawal Form, reason, personal)

937
00:59:29,680 --> 00:59:32,249
I already submitted the withdrawal form.

938
00:59:32,850 --> 00:59:34,251
It'll be official
after a face-to-face talk.

939
00:59:34,251 --> 00:59:35,119
What?

940
00:59:36,787 --> 00:59:37,621
What?

941
00:59:38,589 --> 00:59:39,757
Forget it.

942
00:59:39,757 --> 00:59:41,892
Go back to med school tomorrow.

943
00:59:41,892 --> 00:59:42,793
Go and beg them.

944
00:59:44,028 --> 00:59:45,429
I can't go back.

945
00:59:45,429 --> 00:59:47,531
Why not?

946
00:59:47,531 --> 00:59:49,366
Don't you start causing trouble too, okay?

947
00:59:49,833 --> 00:59:51,435
Go back to med school tomorrow.

948
00:59:51,435 --> 00:59:53,003
I won't tell Mom.

949
00:59:53,003 --> 00:59:55,706
Go take back the withdrawal form.

950
00:59:58,342 --> 00:59:59,276
To tell you the truth...

951
01:00:06,951 --> 01:00:07,818
I...

952
01:00:09,520 --> 01:00:10,521
killed a man.

953
01:00:13,891 --> 01:00:14,758
What?

954
01:00:18,262 --> 01:00:20,731
Seong Ji Cheon. Put the scalpel down.

955
01:00:20,731 --> 01:00:21,765
The patient's blood pressure is dropping.

956
01:00:21,765 --> 01:00:22,633
Right now.

957
01:00:23,901 --> 01:00:25,102
We need to start CPR. Now.

958
01:00:25,102 --> 01:00:26,670
You punk. Can you not hear me?

959
01:00:27,504 --> 01:00:30,307
Can you not hear me? Put down the scalpel!

960
01:00:30,307 --> 01:00:31,141
Put down the scalpel.

961
01:00:42,653 --> 01:00:43,888
Unexpected variables...

962
01:00:44,321 --> 01:00:46,757
always explode from the quietest one.

963
01:01:12,850 --> 01:01:15,786
(Cabbage Your Life)

964
01:01:15,786 --> 01:01:18,289
I ran away because I wanted to hide.

965
01:01:18,822 --> 01:01:21,325
Does it bother you
that I'm going to Seoul?

966
01:01:21,325 --> 01:01:22,927
If Ji Cheon causes a problem too,
I really can't go on.

967
01:01:22,927 --> 01:01:24,595
No, that's not what I meant.

968
01:01:24,595 --> 01:01:26,263
Whatever I do, however I live,

969
01:01:26,263 --> 01:01:27,131
I'll be the one to decide.

970
01:01:27,498 --> 01:01:30,201
What exactly did you do for this family?

971
01:01:30,534 --> 01:01:31,969
From now on,

972
01:01:31,969 --> 01:01:33,637
I'm going to start learning about my sons.

973
01:01:33,637 --> 01:01:35,172
Why are you suddenly
acting like we're close?

974
01:01:35,172 --> 01:01:36,507
Just keep doing what you always did.

975
01:01:36,507 --> 01:01:38,843
What am I supposed to do?

976
01:01:38,843 --> 01:01:41,545
You grew those cabbages
with your sweat and tears.

977
01:01:41,545 --> 01:01:43,547
You want to hand them over
to those people again?

978
01:01:44,215 --> 01:01:45,683
When you said you were going to farm here,

979
01:01:45,683 --> 01:01:47,051
why do you think I was against it?

980
01:01:48,619 --> 01:01:50,621
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)

